      "span_text": "These results support a constant monomer density region comparable to the density of the corresponding polymer melt closest to the core followed by a region of monotonously decreasing monomer density corresponding to that of a star polymer to describe the internal structure and unique colloidal properties of ultradensely grafted core−shell NPs. Our findings demonstrate that SAXS can be applied to structural studies of hybrid core−shell NP systems."
